      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "WYONG GRESHAM (2) missed the frame last time out when sixth at this track from Box eight (31.29) but draws same box here as latest win. Solid record here at the distance winning two races. Has good early burn and is drawn to be prominent. Has ability and can bounce back. SKEDADDLE LOUISE (1) broke a string of placings finishing in the money two on end before a last start fifth (21.23) at Nowra. Form at the trip sound including five wins. Strong form has emerged from her last run. Should play a prominent role. CROYDON (7) jumped cleanly from the rails last start to lead all the way and score (29.31) at Sandown in a Grade 5 over 515m. Good beginner but will need a little luck early crossing from an outside draw. Can measure up again. GINNY'S RUN (3) will be hard to beat despite making her debut at this circuit.",
